Academic Heritage - the Capital of Astana
The Museum of the Book of the National Academic Library in Astana houses the manuscripts, library, and other objects of the outstanding literary scholar, academic Zakhi Akhmetov, from his writing desk to his personal belongings.
The bookstore was given to the museum by the academic's wife, Ziya Nasirovna, four years ago.
This year marks the 90th anniversary of Z. Akhmetov .
The number of well-preserved monuments has been increased.
According to the head of the Museum "Book" Mulder Baymakhanbetova, the library received 43 folders containing the manuscripts of the scientist.
Recently, 67 more folders were delivered.
The academic library has 850 books.
Among them are books signed by teachers such as Mukhtar Auezov, Zhirmunsky, Malov, Manuilov, Nina Smirnova.
Zakhi Akhmetov graduated from school at the age of 14 and graduated from KazMU at the age of 19.
From 1947 to 1950 he studied at the graduate school of the Institute of Oriental Studies in Leningrad.
At the age of 27 he defended his PhD thesis on the topic of "Lermon­tov and Абай".
Before the age of 40, he defended his dissertation "The construction of Kazakh poetry" and obtained the degree of doctor of philology.
Many of his works have survived in manuscript.
He also wrote a number of newspaper articles that were not included in his books.
Now the students are collecting their works and intend to publish 10 volumes , - said M.Baymakhanbetova.
