The rules of combating "black archaeology" are approved.
After the Black Archaeologists, the monuments are being destroyed and left open.
This was announced by Minister of Culture and Sports Arstanbek Mukhamediuly during the presentation of the draft law " On protection and use of historical and cultural heritage objects " in the Majilis .
The issue of regulating archaeological and restoration works on historical and cultural heritage sites requires a review.
It is no secret that our unique monuments or unexplored objects are often searched and excavated by "black archaeologists", after which the monuments are left open and partially or completely destroyed.
In addition, there are also situations where intensive construction works carried out on adjacent territories of historical and cultural heritage objects have a significant impact on the historical integrity and preservation of historical and cultural monuments, leading to negative consequences.
In general, there is a need to strengthen the legal framework, which requires a clear regulation and create favorable conditions for the protection and use of historical and cultural heritage objects, - the minister stressed.
According to him, at the legislative level, it is envisaged to establish the procedure for identification and registration of historical and cultural heritage objects, as well as monitoring their condition, and to introduce new qualitative mechanisms for preserving and using historical heritage objects in their final historical appearance .
In addition, it is proposed to establish rules and conditions for conducting archaeological works and combating "black archaeology", regulate the legal regime of land use in protected areas, construction of historical and cultural monuments, determine the legal regime of use of natural landscape areas.
The draft law was developed with the study of international experience.
For example, Russian legislation includes measures to combat "black archaeology" for illegal archaeological searches, destruction of archaeological objects, avoidance of the transfer of artifacts to the state and others.
In other words, criminal liability is provided.
In Italy, there are obligations for private collectors at the legislative level.
According to them, it is planned to create and periodically update lists of objects of cultural and artistic interest and private property.
In addition , the objects in the property of the owners of these facilities are subject to state protection , regardless of their nationality , citizenship , - said A. Mukhamediuly.
The festival " Holy Kazakh Country " will be held in Astana with participants from 10 countries.
The international festival of arts " Holy Kazakh Country " with the participation of foreign compatriots will be held in the capital , the correspondent of KazAkkart reports .
The festival will be attended by about 50 candidates from 10 countries.
35 of them are from abroad, the rest are from our country.
Our compatriots from France, Afghanistan, Turkey, Iran and other countries are testing the garden.
The competition will be held in three areas: traditional crafts competition, weaving contest and singing contest.
The festival is a remarkable event that takes place every year.
The purpose is to unite our compatriots abroad and glorify our national art together.
This year we decided to hold the contest in Astana.
Next year, we will hold regional festivals in all regions of the country to select the best.
We plan to organize a large-scale festival in Astana at the end of the year , - said the head of the Astana and Akmola regional branch of the World Association of Kazakhs Karligash Bekpatshakovna .
According to the organizers, the art event is important for strengthening relations with compatriots abroad.
And the special thing this year is that it is held for the first time in Astana.
The total prize pool of the international art competition is about 3 million tenge .
The event is organized by the World Association of Kazakhs and the Foundation "Ottandastars" and will be held on November 7 at the Palace of Peace and Reconciliation.
The sponsor is the Ministry of Community Development.
