College leaders are deceiving the country and the government.
The Prosecutor's Office of the East Kazakhstan region has conducted a review of the activities of colleges in the region and identified numerous violations of the law, as well as unintended spending of budget funds.
In particular, there were cases of non-compliance with the competition procedures, false training of students, illegal granting of grants, failure of teachers to meet the qualification requirements, lack of provision of student dormitories, as well as illegal leasing of state property.
The number of graduates employed in the country has been artificially increased by recruitment, and the administration of educational institutions has often not helped graduates to find employment.
Despite the fact that the rules for placing state educational orders were violated and students from other places were not provided with dormitories, the regional education department annually awarded grants to the College of Business and Service of Semipalatinsk, the Polytechnic College of Ayagoz and two colleges in Uzhbekistan.
The administration of the college included costs for the services included in the total amount of the contract for the cost of student accommodation in the dormitories, renting rooms in the dormitories to third parties.
He lied to 12 students at a college in Cornwall.
Teachers and masters of industrial training evaluated these students in theoretical and practical study journals during the course of the course, sent them to interim certification, transferred them from one course to another.
In addition, scholarships were paid to these students and the total amount of damage to the state amounted to 8 million tenge.
A pre-trial investigation is underway.
The College has also identified illegal use of property for private purposes.
For example, a paid parking lot has been located on the territory of the East Kazakhstan Regional Art School named after the brothers Abdulinders.
After the introduction of the Prosecutor's recommendation, the parking lot is planned to be closed and a sports field will be built in its place.
According to the results of the investigation , prosecutors have determined damages of more than 43 million tenge .
According to the supervisory acts , 36 million tenge have been recovered to date .
60 persons were brought to disciplinary and 4 persons to administrative responsibility .
